result.execSummary:
The defendant Vernon J Dvorak Jr. was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Vernon J Dvorak Jr. is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Vernon J Dvorak Jr. was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th w/ Passenger < 16 Yrs Old), an unclassified felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).
  • Vernon J Dvorak Jr. was found guilty of Operating While Revoked (Rev due to alc/contr subst/refusal), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Vernon J Dvorak in court, in custody from FC jail with attorney Mary L.R. Burns.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called 2:17 PM. State - has agreement, has filed exhibit #1 with court, certified driving record. No objecttion from Burns. Court accepts exhibit #1. Count 1 - defendant would enter guilty plea. Count 2 to be dimsissed. Count 3 - defendant would enter a guilty plea. Count 1 - State asks for consecutive time on revocation, Burns free to argue for concurrent time on revocation. Burns indicates he has not been revoked yet. Recommendation: sentence to the Wisconsin Prision System for 6 years - 3 years of incarrceration, 3 years extended supervision, fine of $6000, $35 restitution for City of Crandon for blood draw, 6 yr. DL suspension, IID leave time up to court, DOC to set condition for ES. Burns agrees with recommendation. Court dimisses Count 2. Counts 1 & 3 - defendant pleas guilty. Burns has provided court with plea questionnaire, court goes over form with Dvorak and finds the defendant is freely, voluntairly and inteligently entering his plea and right to JT. Court accepts plea, finds factual basis and adjudges guilty. Defendant acknowledges 5 prior OWI's. State - makes final statement and asks court to follow recommendation. Burns makes final statement, asks to follow joint recommendation and asks that defendant be eligible for early release program and substance abuse program. Dvorak makes statement. Court has considered all statements of parties, court accepts joint recommendation and sentences the defendant to the following: Count 1 - Impose 6 years in the Wisconsin Prision System - 3 years of incarrceration followed by 3 years of extended supervision, fine of $6000, $35 restitution to City of Crandon for blood draw, revoke DL for 6 years, IID 3 years - upon issuance of a valid DL and installed on any vehicle registered or titled in defendants name, AODA and follow through with any recommendations. State argues that he not be eligible for at least 2 years for the early release program. Court does not authorize defendant eligible for either program. Stipulated 87 days of jail credit. Voting and firearm rights given. Must submit DNA. Right to appeal.
#1 - BAC results; #2 - copy of search warrant for blood draw

Defendant Vernon J Dvorak in court with attorney Mary L.R. Burns.  Defendant Vernon J Dvorak in custody.   Charles Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 10:14 AM. State - defense will stipulate to 5 prior OWI convictions of record for today's proceedings only. Court accepts stipulation. State calls Officer Eric Bath. Bath sworn in at 10:14 AM. Direct exam by State. Burns - objection to double hearsay - overruled (10:19 AM). Record reflects proper identification of the defendant (10:24 AM). State offers exhibit #1 - blood draw results of the defendant. Court receives exhibit #1 after no objections (10:25 AM). State offers exhibit #2 - search warrant for blood draw. Court receives exhibit #2 after no objections (10:27 AM). Cross exam by Burns at 10:27 AM. Bath excused at 10:31 AM. Court finds probable cause that a felony was committed, binds over for trial. State has Information but will be filing an Amended Information that will include the PAC charge, at this point the Information being filed mirrors the complaint at this point. Burns will proceed to ARGN, has Information, waives reading of it, enters NG pelas to all counts. Court accepts pleas, continues bond at this point, sets for FPT.  Final pre-trial scheduled for December 2, 2015 at 02:30 pm.

Defendant Vernon J Dvorak in court with attorney Mary L.R. Burns.  Defendant Vernon J Dvorak in custody and appears via video from FOSO.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 9:48 AM. Burns and Dvorak have complaint, waives reading of it, requests PH but willing to waive time limits. Dvorak does not want to waive time limits. Court continues bond, set for PH.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for October 2, 2015 at 10:00 am.

Defendant Vernon J Dvorak in court, in custody and appears via video from FOSO and without counsel.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called 9:55 AM. Defendant does not have copy of complaint. State will provide one to the jail. Court reads charges, pentalties and right to attorney. Dvorak understands and would like an attorney. Court informs defendant of SPD and court appointed attorney. State bond - no objection to continuing bond as is. Court continues bond.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for September 30, 2015 at 09:15 am.
